<HL> Who's News: Cyprus Minerals' Unit Breaks Into 3 Concerns </HL>
<SO> </SO>
<CO> CYPM WNEWS </CO>
<DATELINE> DENVER  </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Cyprus Minerals Co. said it will form three new operating companies out of its Cyprus Metals Co. unit and named executives to head them. 

   F. Steven Moone, senior vice president of the metals unit, will be executive vice president and chief operating officer of the new Cyprus Copper Co. Michael D. Martin, currently a vice president of Cyprus Metals, will be executive vice president and chief operating officer of the new Cyprus Gold Co. 

   And Thomas A. Williams, currently president of Exton, Pa.-based Foote Mineral Co., will be executive vice president and chief operating officer of Cyprus Specialty Metals Co., which will operate the company's lithium and beryllium properties and a molybdenum processing business. 
Cyprus acquired 82% of Foote in February. 

   The company said it will also form a metals development group to identify and develop metals properties in the U.S. and Mexico. 
C.W. Reno, formerly general manager of the company's Sierrita copper mine near Tucson, Ariz., will be executive vice president of that group. 

   Cyprus said it is setting up the operating units because its business is growing rapidly. 
Over the past year, the company has purchased several new mining properties and has increased its gold production. 
Operating earnings for the metals unit more than doubled to $31.9 million for 1987 from $15.8 million for 1986. 

   The company produces gold, copper, coal, molybdenum and industrial minerals. 

