<TEXT>
   Amax Inc. said it will suspend operations at a Colorado molybdenum mine and close another for a week, and will cut 220 employees from its workforce to bring supply and demand for the metal into closer balance. 

   The metal and minerals concern said its Climax mine near Leadville will be closed Friday for an indefinite period. 
The weeklong closure of the Henderson mine near Empire will begin March 23. 

   By the end of March, the Climax workforce of 200 will be reduced to about 50, required for security and maintenance, Amax said. 
The Henderson workforce will be cut to 620 from 690, including managers and hourly workers. 

   Amax had a 1986 loss of $65.8 million on sales of $1.3 billion. 

