<TEXT>
   Cyprus Minerals Co. said it reorganized its executive management as part of an effort to reduce costs, focus its marketing efforts and "place more responsibility for growth through strategic acquisitions at the corporate level." 

   The minerals concern, with interests in coal, copper, molybdenum, gold and industrial minerals, said the changes are effective Oct. 4. 

   Donald P. Bellum, formerly president of its Cyprus Coal Co. unit, was named an executive vice president of Cyprus Minerals, with responsiblity over the company's Cyprus Coal and Cyprus Industrial Minerals Co. units. 
Donald P. Brown, formerly vice president of coal operations for Cyprus Coal, succeeds Mr. Bellum and will report to him. 

   Philip C. Wolf, senior vice president of law and human resources, becomes president of the company's Cyprus Industrial Minerals Co. unit and also will report to Mr. Bellum. 
Mr. Wolf succeeds H.T. Mulryan, who was named to the new post of senior vice president of marketing and corporate administration, with responsibility for the marketing efforts of the company's three operating units. 

   James C. Compton, president of the company's Cyprus Metals Co. unit, was named to the additional post of executive vice president of Cyprus Minerals. 

   Gerard H. Peppard, manager of human resources, was given the additional title of vice president of human resources. 

</TEXT>
