<TEXT>
   Amax Inc., Greenwich, Conn., will expand its Sleeper gold mine in Nevada at a cost of $17 million, Allen Born, president and chief executive officer, told the annual meeting in New York. 

   The expansion will boost the mine's total annual production about 20% to an estimated 250,000 ounces by year end. 
Mr. Born said the energy and metals company is benefiting from increased prices. 
With the company's restructuring of the past two years largely completed, he expects 1988 to be "an excellent year" in terms of profit and sales, but he wouldn't make a projection. 
In 1987, the company earned $51.2 million, or 53 cents a share, on sales of $3.38 billion. 

   Amax's main businesses are aluminum, energy, gold and molybdenum. 

