<IN> ERN MIN </IN>
<TEXT>
   Amax Inc. reported its fourth-quarter net loss widened to $280.8 million, reflecting a $385.6 million write-down of molybdenum assets. 

   In the year-earlier period, the Greenwich, Conn.-based minerals and energy concern had a net loss of $49.7 million. 
Sales more than doubled to $912.4 million from $423.2 million. 

   For all of 1987, the company reported net income more than tripled to $51.2 million, or 53 cents a share, from $14.3 million, or five cents a share. 
Sales more than doubled to $3.4 billion from $1.3 billion. 

   Amax attributed the 1987 improvement to better results from aluminum and gold operations. 

   In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday, Amax's stock closed at $17.75, down 50 cents. 

